               <msContents>
                  <summary>Thirty-three Miracles of Mary, ተአምረ፡ ማርያም፡; Five Miracles of Michael, ተአምረ፡ ሚካኤል፡; Three Miracles of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus, ተአምረ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡; Three Miracles of Jesus, ተአምረ፡ ኢየሱስ፡; One Miracle of Abunä Zär’a Buruk, ተአምረ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘርዓ፡ ቡሩክ፡</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="43r" facs="004">Fols 1r–43r</locus>
                  <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2384Taamme">Taʾammǝra
                                                  Māryām</title>
                  <note>Thirty-Three Miracles of Mary</note>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                      <locus from="1r" to="7r" facs="004">Fols 1r–7r</locus>
                      <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6024IntroMM">Introductory text
                                                  and hymn to the Miracles of Mary</title>
                    </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                      <locus from="8r" to="43r" facs="018">Fols 8r–43r</locus>
                      <note>Miracles, each with a greeting, beginning at
                        <locus target="#8r #9v #10v #11r #12r #13r #14r #15r #16r #16v #18v #19r #20r #20v #22r #22v #24r #25r #26r #26v #27v #29r #30r #30v #32r                           #34r #35r #36r #38v #39v #40v #41r #41v" facs="018 021 023 024 026 028 030 032 034 035 039 040 042 043 046 047 050 052 054 055 057 060 062 063 066 070 072 074 079 081 083 084 085">fols. 8r, 9v, 10v, 11r, 12r, 13r, 14r, 15r, 16r, 16v, 18v, 19r, 20r, 20v, 22r, 22v, 24r, 25r, 26r, 26v, 27v, 29r, 30r, 30v, 32r,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, ,, , 34r, 35r, 36r, 38v, 39v, 40v, 41r, 41v</locus>
                          </note>
                    </msItem>
                  </msItem>

               <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                 <locus from="44r" to="47v" facs="090">Fols 44r–47v</locus>
                  <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5066MiraclesMichael">Miracles of
                                                  Michael</title>
                  <note>Five miracles of Michael, each miracle has a greeting at <locus target="#44r #44v #45v #46r #47r">fols. 44r, 44v, 45v, 46r, 47r</locus></note>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.1">
                      <locus from="44r" to="44v" facs="090">Fols 44r–44v</locus>
                    <title>How the Archangel Michael saved people in Egypt when their ship was caught in a storm in the middle of the sea</title></msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.2">
                      <locus from="44v" to="45v" facs="091">Fols 44v–45v</locus>
                      <title>How the Archangel Michael appeared to a certain man who celebrated his feast every month, but in that season had lost his crops because of drought;
                        how the Archangel Michael commanded him to go fishing and how he caught a great fish and found a chest of gold in the mouth of the fish</title></msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.3">
                      <locus from="45v" to="46r" facs="093">Fols 45v–46r</locus>
                    <title>How the Archangel Michael gave a blessing to a certain farmer who lost his crops to a devouring worm</title></msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.4">
                      <locus from="46r" to="46v" facs="094">Fols 46r–46v</locus>
                    <title>How the Archangel Michael appeared to a devout man who was sick and how he healed him</title></msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.5">
                      <locus from="47r" to="46v" facs="096">Fols 47r–46v</locus>
                    <title>How the Archangel Michael appeared at a certain church when a man possessed by an evil spirit came to the church and challenged the authority of the Archangel;
                      and how the Archangel cured the man</title></msItem>
                </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                    <locus from="47v" to="49v" facs="097">Fols 47v–49v</locus>
                  <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3977Taammer">Taʾammǝra Gabra
                                                  Manfas Qǝddus</title>
                  <note>Three Miracles of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus</note>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.1">
                      <locus from="47v" to="48v" facs="097">Fols 47v–48v</locus>
                      <title>How Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus cast out a demon from a certain woman who suffered for three years from this evil spirit</title>
                    </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.2">
                      <locus from="48v" to="49r" facs="099">Fols 48v–49r</locus>
                      <title>How a certain man was on his way to the church during the feast of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus and a bird took his baptismal necklace of yarn (ማህተም);
                        how the man beseeched the bird by the power of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus; and how, when he returned from the church, the bird was dead and the scarf was
                        there (MYS 24, ff. 160rv)</title>
                    </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.3">
                      <locus from="49r" to="49v" facs="100">Fols 49r–49v</locus>
                      <title>How Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus raised a dead child when his mother prayer to the saint</title>
                    </msItem>
                </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                    <locus from="49v" to="52r" facs="101">Fols 49v–52r</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2382Taamme">Taʾammǝra
                                                  ʾIyasus</title>
                      <note>Three miracles of Jesus</note>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i4.1"><locus from="49v" facs="101">Fols 49v and following</locus><title>While he was a child, how he graciously cared for his servant</title></msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i4.2"><locus from="50r" facs="102">Fols 50r and following</locus><title>The acount of the census that was ordered when time of the birth of Our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ approached</title></msItem>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i4.3"><locus from="51v" facs="105">Fols 51v and following</locus><title>When Joseph of Arimathea, and his relative Nicodemus, brother of Cliopas came to take the body of Jesus</title></msItem>
                </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                    <locus from="52v" to="56r" facs="107">Fols 52v–56r</locus>
                    <title>One Miracle of Abunä Zär’a Buruk, Tä’ammǝrä Abunä Zär’a Buruk, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተአምረ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘርዓ፡ ቡሩክ፡</foreign>
                    How, when Abunä Zär’a Buruk died, his spiritual children came from around the world, and many miracles occurred;
                    and how many people were raised from the dead.
                  </title>
                </msItem>
               </msContents>
